OL,3,CPost Office compensation still moving
OL,4,Cfar too slowly, MPs warn
OL,6,FThe data also says that of the 492
OL,7,Fsubpostmasters who joined Sir Alan
OL,8,FBates in taking the Post Office to
OL,9,Fcourt between 2017 and 2019 that have
OL,10,Fnot been convicted, also known as the
OL,11,FGroup Litigation Order Scheme (GLO),
OL,12,F488 have received #167 million between
OL,13,Fthem.
OL,15,FElsewhere, #245 million has been paid
OL,16,Fout to 463 subpostmasters who had
OL,17,Ftheir convictions quashed by
OL,18,Flegislation put in place last summer,
OL,19,Fand #68 million has been paid to those
OL,20,Fwho have had their convictions quashed
OL,21,Fin the courts.
